<h1>Getting Started</h1>

<ol>
    <li>
        <p>Installing via <i>bower</i> is the simplest form:</p>
        <pre><code class="bash">bower install ember-forms</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Include Bootstrap for styling</p>
        <pre><code class="html">&lt;link href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"&gt;</code></pre>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Include Ember Forms</p>
        <pre><code class="html">&lt;script src="bower_components/ember-forms/dist/ember_forms.js"&gt;</script></code></pre>
    </li>
</ol>

<p>Of course you need jquery, ember.js and handlebars included in your project too.</p>


